curl -XPOST 'http://localhost:9200/electronic_products/_create/2616' -H 'Content-Type: application/json' -d '{"product_name": "SGM4552", "table_name": "TITLE", "content": "  SGM4552  1-Bit Bidirectional Voltage-Level Translator  for Open-Drain and Push-Pull Applications      SG Micro Corp  www.sg-micro.com  JUNE2014–REV.A  "}'
curl -XPOST 'http://localhost:9200/electronic_products/_create/2617' -H 'Content-Type: application/json' -d '{"product_name": "SGM4552", "table_name": "GENERAL DESCRIPTION", "content": "GENERAL DESCRIPTION  The SGM4552 is a 1-bit, non-inverting, bidirectional  voltage-level translator which features two independent  configurable power-supply lines. The A and B ports  track the VCCA supply and VCCB supply respectively. The  supply voltage range is 1.65V to 5.5V for A port and  2.3V to 5.5V for B port. The device provides a  bidirectional translation function between the different  voltage nodes (including 1.8V, 2.5V, 3.3V and 5V).  The SGM4552 has an output enable (OE) function,  which controls the inputs and outputs states. When OE  goes low, all I/Os enter into the high-impedance state. It is  beneficial for reducing quiescent current consumption.  When VCCA is powered, OE has an internal pull-down  current source.  The SGM4552 is available in Green SOT-23-6, SC70-6  and UTDFN-1.45×1-6L packages. It operates over an  ambient temperature range of -40℃ to +85℃.  "}'
curl -XPOST 'http://localhost:9200/electronic_products/_create/2618' -H 'Content-Type: application/json' -d '{"product_name": "SGM4552", "table_name": "FEATURES", "content": "FEATURES  ● Power Supply Voltage Ranges (VCCA ≤ VCCB)   A Port: 1.65V to 5.5V   B Port: 2.3V to 5.5V  ● Direction-Control Signal is Not Required  ● Data Rates   Push-Pull: 24Mbps   Open-Drain: 2Mbps  ● Support VCCA or VCCB Isolation   When VCCA or VCCB is Low, Device Enters  Power-Down Mode  ● No Specific Power Sequences Required for VCCA  and VCCB  ● Support Power-Down Mode  ● -40℃ to +85℃ Operating Temperature Range  ● Available in Green UTDFN-1.45×1-6L, SOT-23-6  and SC70-6 Packages    "}'
